<task id="WKSP-050" project="spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Support workspaceId URL parameter for deep-linking</title>
    <phase>6</phase>
    <tags>frontend, integration</tags>
    <estimated-effort>3h</estimated-effort>
    <rigor-level>STANDARD</rigor-level>
    <dependencies>032</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>E</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <role>Senior developer implementing workspace personalization</role>
    <goal>Support a workspaceId URL parameter so that direct links can open a specific workspace layout instead of the user's default.</goal>
    <context>
      The LegalWorkspace is loaded as a Dataverse webresource. URL parameters are passed via the
      Xrm data parameter (query string encoded). When a workspaceId is present, the workspace should
      load that specific layout instead of the user's default.

      This enables scenarios like: sharing a link to a specific workspace view, bookmarking a
      preferred layout, or navigating back to a specific workspace from another page.

      If the specified workspaceId is invalid or the layout doesn't exist (deleted, or belongs to
      another user), the workspace should gracefully fall back to the user's default layout.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - MUST parse workspaceId from Xrm data parameter (URL query string)
      - MUST fetch the specific layout by ID from GET /api/workspace/layouts/{id}
      - MUST fall back to user's default layout if workspaceId is invalid or layout not found
      - MUST NOT show an error dialog for missing layouts — silent fallback with console.warn
      - MUST update the WorkspaceHeader dropdown to reflect the deep-linked layout as active
      - MUST work with the existing useWorkspaceLayouts hook from Task 032
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-026-full-page-custom-page-standard.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/LegalWorkspaceApp.tsx</file>
    <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/main.tsx</file>
  </relevant-files>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read the existing main.tsx to understand how Xrm data parameters are currently parsed (if at all) and how the app receives initialization context.</step>
    <step id="2">Add workspaceId extraction from the Xrm data parameter: parse the data query string, extract workspaceId value if present.</step>
    <step id="3">Update the useWorkspaceLayouts hook to accept an optional initialWorkspaceId parameter. When provided, attempt to fetch that specific layout first.</step>
    <step id="4">Add fallback logic: if the deep-linked layout fetch returns 404 or fails, console.warn and fall back to the default layout selection flow.</step>
    <step id="5">Ensure the WorkspaceHeader dropdown reflects the deep-linked layout as the active selection.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Navigating with workspaceId parameter loads the specified layout instead of default</criterion>
    <criterion>Invalid or missing workspaceId falls back to default layout without error dialog</criterion>
    <criterion>WorkspaceHeader dropdown shows the deep-linked layout as active</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
